Binghamton University Libraries=92 presents Funding=20
Our Digital Future: Budgeting for Libraries &=20
Scholarly Communication on March 20-21, 2006 at Binghamton University=92s=
 campus.

The purpose of the symposium will be:
    * To explore the challenges of library=20
resource allocation in the digital age
    * To create a flexible resource allocation=20
process to respond to changing research and=20
curricular needs of faculty and students, to=20
address the increasing interdisciplinary nature=20
of teaching and research, and to involve the=20
university community in an ongoing dialogue with=20
the University Libraries in this process.
    * To address the broad issues of the changing=20
nature of scholarship in the digital age; both=20
the production of scholarly information and the=20
communication of scholarship within the academic=20
community (e.g. the open-access initiative and=20
its funding model implications for libraries and=20
universities) and how these impact the challenges=20
facing libraries in collection resource=20
management and the strategies used to address these challenges.
There is no registration fee.
